  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "E.g. MIN_INT128, MAX_INT128, etc. These were added to reduce code size, but with constantinople we now use bit shifting to calculate the constants. For pre-constantinople targets, we should emulate SHR/SHL/SAR with the following rewrites:\r\n```\r\nshr x y -> (div x (pow 2 y))\r\nshl x y -> (mul x (pow 2 y))\r\nsar x y -> (sdiv x (pow 2 y))\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis saves us several memory slots and will simplify the codebase.",
